name: God's Pantry
review_text: Lots of food and chaotic place, intimidating for the beginner,  D minus In logistics . Nobody knows what‚Äôs going on , clients and hoarders get into  fights due to the long-waiting. There is not a schedule neither online or on site that can tell you or explain to you what is offered . Lots of goodies clothes, food but the dozens of people waiting to get in do not have a clue about what they are going to get . The volunteer desk lacks proper attention . Volunteers show up and they are just waiting for someone to tell them what to do . Nobody cares and there is a feeling of chaos at the same time. There are a couple politicians taking their pictures here and there and posing for a picture . Go to this place only if you need food You need an appointment to get a bag of food and it is drive thru only, you can expect bumper to bumper drive. Food is in general good but you either cook it the same day or freeze it. Volunteers and staff are not very helpful. Remember, it is drive thru only, do not bring kids with you , the waiting time can be long and the driving can get very tedious
